Disappointing is all I can say. I was excited to try this place after seeing all of the positive reviews. The poor experience has more to do with the service than the food. First, i ordered a few tacos, the crab tostadas, the chicken enchiladas with mole pablano, and a happy hour beer. The tacos were very good, not the most authentic, but very flavorful - the pork tacos were the best. The crab tostada was bland and boring, but they were only $11 so I'm not trowing a fit. The real problem came with the entree. The enchiladas were bland and had a terrible aftertaste, as if something was off. I've had mole pablano before, but I did not enjoy this sauce. It was drenched over the bland chicken enchiladas and then a handful of sesame seeds were thrown on top. The plate was inedible so I notified my waiter. Noticeably shaken, he said "one moment" and went to the kitchen to grab who i assumed was the cook/manager. This lady told me that "this is how it's always made and everyone likes it." She then proceeded to tell me that she was not going to give me "free food." I politely explained that I did not want free food and that, while I respect that other people may enjoy the dish, I did not enjoy it. I only had a bite, and would have appreciated at least a dish swap. She did not exchange the dish and did not comp the food. To top it off, she laughed at me when I told her that this wasn't great service. I will never go back. Too bad.

Visited twice this year and had an excellent meals. On my first visit I had the fish taco as an appetizer and the chicken mole entree. On the second visit I had the pork and beef tacos. I went during lunch hours and it was not crowded at all.

So, here's the deal you should try the chicken taco and pork taco. The chicken taco is well seasoned with fresh ingredients avocado, cheese,etc. The pork taco has pineapple salsa on it with sliced boiled onion. The touch of pineapple with the red onion gives it a sweet touch that's not overbearing. I recommend this restaurant. They have a lovely indoor bar.

Maybe ordered wrong, but not that impressed. As an app I had the tamale with chorizo and mussels. Frankly the only tamale I've ever really enjoyed was from a woman with a street cart in Queens who made her tamales with lots of lard, so that the tamale was smooth and rich tasting. This tamale was moist and came in a sauce that would have been tasty if not for the fact that the mussels added a fishy taste. For the main I had the chicken enchiladas with mole sauce: dry shredded chicken that didn't seem to have actually been cooked in the sauce (which could have used a bit of thickening) and tortillas with a gooey texture. Oh well.

Wanted to go to a place the day before valentines day that was close by because of the extreme cold. I found this gem by Google search near me. It had nothing but five star reviews. I have never noticed this place before. So glad I found it. We were greeted right away and seated. The staff is very friendly very, family like. The décor made me feel like I was in Williamsburg - small but cute. We ordered a whole bunch of different things off their menu. Everything was amazing!! It was very different then any Mexican place I ever been too. They definitely have a different taste style. But I love it something different for a change and it hit every taste bud. Everything was super fresh and made to order. Highly recommend. I am craving there guacamole and nachos as I am typing this lol. They deliver too! Yessss!!

Amazing find! The food is exceptional -- creative but also authentic Mexican. This is not your average burrito joint -- this is a true gem! The real deal.  There's not a lot of atmosphere, but the surprisingly elegant plates of deeply flavored cuisine and the warm, excellent service more than make up for it. We also liked the byob policy, and they even gave us some limes to go with our coronas (which we bought at the deli right across the street).  The FISH TACOS!! maybe some of the best I've ever had. The roasted cauliflower and unique sauce really make them amazing. I also thought the yucca fries were perfect -- crispy and salty with plenty of that wonderful yucca texture and flavor that I love. The "Garden" dish was a hearty mix of vegetables over a fantastic "green mole" -- a uniquely satisfying vegan option.  Can't wait to go back!
The food is great, guacamole and chips are amazing!! The staff are very friendly. I love this place!!!
